<Layout title="About - Map the Wild">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-space">
    <div class="stars"></div>
    <div class="stars2"></div>
    <div class="stars3"></div>

    <main class="relative z-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-12">
        About
      </h1>

      <article class="prose prose-invert space-y-6 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I make prototypes. Mostly things that mess with how people see their relationships, careers, or their own thinking. Not productivity stuff. Not capture-more-data stuff.
        </p>

        <p>
          This is where I put them. Along with some writing about why I made them and what I learned.
        </p>

        <p>
          The name: I like the idea that knowledge is territory, not a database. You walk around in it. Most of it is unmapped. The good parts are usually off the path.
        </p>

        <p>
          Things I work on:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-400">
          <li>Tools that show you how you think (not what to think)</li>
          <li>Structured rituals for couples and individuals</li>
          <li>Figuring out what's actually useful vs what AI just generates</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="pt-8">
          <a href="/mapthewild/posts" class="text-white hover:text-gray-300 transition-colors">
            View all posts â†’
          </a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>

